Package: nex2426
Version: 0.1.0
Section: security
Priority: optional
Architecture: amd64
Depends: libc6 (>= 2.31), libgcc-s1 (>= 4.2)
Maintainer: NEX2426 Development Team <dev@nex2426.io>
Homepage: https://github.com/nex2426/nex2426
Description: Quantum-Resistant Chaos Encryption Engine
 NEX2426 is a sophisticated encryption system that provides
 multiple layers of security against both classical and quantum
 computer attacks.
 .
 Features:
  • Post-quantum lattice-based cryptography
  • Chaos-based non-linear transformations
  • White-box obfuscation techniques
  • Memory-hardening against hardware attacks
  • Temporal binding for non-repudiation
  • File encryption with bio-lock and stealth modes
  • Interactive shell for real-time hashing
  • Performance benchmarking tools
  • Quantum-resistant blockchain implementation
 .
 This package includes the complete NEX2426 engine with
 command-line interface, documentation, and system integration
 components suitable for production deployment.
